<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" Description="The following CALS were changed: KeMMMR_l_ElectRangeMin, KeMMMR_l_FuelRangeMin, KeMMMR_l_RouteMax, KeMMMR_l_RouteMin.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>7</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>1</Version>
    <Date>6/21/2016</Date>
    <Description>Initial release of this caldef file.</Description>
    <Author>Shanmukh Rajurs</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <Date>10/18/2016</Date>
    <Description>The following CALS have been added: MyModeNormalMapping, MyModeHoldMapping, KeMMMR_k_CnvrtSpdHst, KeMMMR_k_CnvrtSpdLmt, KeMMMR_k_CnvrtSpdLv, KeMMMR_k_GrdMinMax, KeMMMR_l_EngOffMxBtwnEvnts, KeMMMR_l_RouteMax, KeMMMR_l_RouteMin, KeMMMR_l_TmBlndLrnDstMx, KeMMMR_P_LrnMinPwr, KeMMMR_P_RstCbnCndng, KeMMMR_P_RstRdLd, KeMMMR_P_RstTtlPwr, KeMMMR_r_MinDstDlt, KeMMMR_r_MinTmDlt, KeMMMR_r_TmBlndRscl, KeMMMR_T_Heat_MaxECT, KeMMMR_T_MinTrnsLrn, KeMMMR_t_RstTm, KeMMMR_t_TmBttnPrss, KnMMMR_v_TrnsTWrmUpSpd, KnMMMR_v_RdLdSpeed, KtMMMR_k_GrdMult, KtMMMR_P_RdLdNominal, KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss. The following CALS have been deleted: KeMMMR_k_GrdMult, KeMMMR_l_RouteMax, KeMMMR_l_RouteMin, KeMMMR_P_RdLdDdBnd, KeMMMR_T_Heat_MaxECT, KeMMMR_T_MinOATLrn, KeMMMR_T_MinTrnsLrn, KeMMMR_t_TmBttnPrss, KnMMMR_v_RdLdSpeed, KtMMMR_P_RdLdNominal, KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss. The following CALS have been changed (updated: type, min, max, resolution, units, and default value): KeMMMR_l_ElectRangeMin, KeMMMR_l_FuelRangeMin, KeMMMR_M_MinAxlTrq, KeMMMR_P_HPThresh, KeMMMR_P_LPThresh, KeMMMR_t_TmBttnPrss, KeMMMR_v_HSThresh, KeMMMR_v_LSThresh, KnMMMR_T_CbnTmp, KnMMMR_T_TrnsTmp, KnMMMR_v_DltaSpd, KtMMMR_E_PwrDltSpd, KtMMMR_k_TrnsTmpMult, KtMMMR_k_TrnsTWrmUp, KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn. </Description>
    <Author>Shanmukh Rajurs</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>1/06/2017</Date>
    <Description>The following CALS were changed: KeMMMR_l_ElectRangeMin, KeMMMR_l_FuelRangeMin, KeMMMR_l_RouteMax, KeMMMR_l_RouteMin.</Description>
    <Author>Shanmukh Rajurs</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>3/1/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS674_MyMode.caldef as reviewed with Shanmukh Rajurs (GIS-674 Spec. owner ) and other team members working on MyMode made the following updates within GIS674_MyMode.caldef file: Updated the allowable minimum value defined for the KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn float array calibration from a minumum value of 1.4E-45 to 0. Note, this update had to made to correct an issue with the default value for one of the array parameters (KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn[2]=0.0 ) needed being below the predefined allowable/workable minimum value. Also, updated the allowable minimum value from a minumum value of 1.4E-45 to 0 defined for the following four float array calibrations: (1) KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss, (2) KtMMMR_P_RdLdNominal, (3) KtMMMR_k_TrnsTWrmUp, (4) KnMMMR_v_RdLdSpeed. Note, made this update as a result of the needed use case of another float array calibration (KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn )within this caldef file having a default value of zero, also updated the minimum value of these four float array calibration (  1.) KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss, 2.) KtMMMR_P_RdLdNominal, 3.) KtMMMR_k_TrnsTWrmUp, and 4.) KnMMMR_v_RdLdSpeed ) to also allow the flexibltiy to set one of the array parameters for these calibration to zero in the future via a CAL override if it were to ever be needed too.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>27MAR2019</Date>
    <Description>Added 'ENTRY_VCU' and 'VCU' tags for initial creation of VCS compatible CalDefDatabase for version GIS-646 V6.0.0 release.</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
