  <CalDefinition Description="The Power lost to SpinLoss as a function of modeled Transmission temperature. (Note: Unit for this CAL is kW)" Name="KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss" References="GIS 674" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_86XrsJSEEeaIoZ25tPZZ7w</CalID>
    <Type>FloatArray</Type>
    <Version>2</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>10/18/2016</Date>
      <Description>Initial Release</Description>
      <Author>Shanmukh Rajurs</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>2</Version>
      <Date>3/1/2017</Date>
      <Description>With agreement from Shanmukh Rajurs and Terry Meehan, updated the allowable minimum value defined for the KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss float array calibration from a minumum value of 1.4E-45 to 0. Note, made this update as a result of the needed use case of another float array calibration (KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn )within this caldef file having a default value of zero, also updated the minimum value of this float array calibration (KtMMMR_P_SpinLoss) to also allow the flexibltiy to set one of the array parameters for this calibration to zero in the future via a CAL override if it were to ever be needed too.</Description>
      <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
    </CalDefChangeRecord>
    <FloatArray>
      <ArrayLength>12</ArrayLength>
      <MinValue>0.0</MinValue>
      <MaxValue>3.4028235E38</MaxValue>
      <Resolution>1.0E-4</Resolution>
      <ArrayValue>0.049999997</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.099999994</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.16</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.24</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.34</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.45999998</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.59</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.68</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>0.92999995</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>1.16</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>1.41</ArrayValue>
      <ArrayValue>1.67</ArrayValue>
    </FloatArray>
  </CalDefinition>
  <CalDefinition Description="Time to switch from Power to Reach Cabin Temperature to Power to Maintain Cabin Temp as a function of Cabin Temperature. (Note: Unit for this CAL is seconds)" Name="KtMMMR_t_HVACSwtchMntn" References="GIS674" Usage="MID,HIGH,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,VCU">
    <CalID>_VLeqYBIIEea9zbViOphNRQ</CalID>
